@startuml
left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

cloud "Internet / Public" as ZInternet
rectangle "DMZ Zone\n(WAF, Reverse Proxy, Edge LB)" as ZDMZ
rectangle "Ecommerce Zone\n(API Gateway, Checkout, Order)" as ZEcom
rectangle "Enterprise Zone\n(Internal Apps, Ops Portals)" as ZEnt
rectangle "Extranet Zone\n(Partner Gateway, B2B APIs)" as ZExtra
database "Data Zone\n(DB, Cache, Warehouse)" as ZData
rectangle "Management/Ops Zone\n(CI/CD, Monitoring, Bastion)" as ZMgmt

ZInternet --> ZDMZ : Inbound HTTPS only
ZDMZ --> ZEcom : Filtered app traffic
ZEcom --> ZData : Least-privilege DB access
ZEcom --> ZExtra : Partner calls via gateway
ZEnt --> ZEcom : Internal user/admin APIs
ZEnt --> ZData : Approved read/write paths
ZMgmt --> ZEcom : Admin/observability control plane
ZMgmt --> ZData : Break-glass + backup ops

note right of ZDMZ
No direct DMZ -> Data access
end note

note bottom of ZEcom
All zone-to-zone traffic is allowlisted
by firewall rules and routing policy.
end note
@enduml

